


State Tax Calculation

```python
from tax.state.colorado.rules import ColoradoTaxRules

co_tax = ColoradoTaxRules()

# Calculate Colorado income tax
co_income_tax = co_tax.calculate_income_tax(
    taxable_income=Decimal('75000'),
    filing_status="single",
    year=2026
)

print(f"Colorado tax: ${co_income_tax['tax_amount']:.2f}")
print(f"Tax rate: {co_income_tax['tax_rate']}%")

# Calculate sales tax
sales_tax = co_tax.calculate_sales_tax(
    purchase_amount=Decimal('100'),
    location="DENVER",
    product_type="general"
)

print(f"Total sales tax: ${sales_tax['total_tax']:.2f}")
print(f"Total rate: {sales_tax['total_tax_rate']}%")
```
